<H3> <TI>   NSC Official Meets With Ukraine's Ambassador </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203130894 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 18 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> AU2203130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by the Press Center of Ukraine's Ministry of </F>
Foreign Affairs: "A Briefing by the Ambassador"] 
  [Text] Ukraine's Ambassador in Poland H. Udovenko 
met with J. Milewski, the leader of the National Security 
Council [NSC], subordinated to the Polish president. Milewski 
is also deputy minister of defense and cochairman of the 
Ukrainian and Polish Presidents' Consultative Committee. The 
Polish leader showed interest in the ambassador's briefing on 
the results of President L. Kravchuk's visit to the United 
States. He also stressed that President L. Walesa had 
repeatedly stated that Ukraine's sovereignty, independence, and 
territorial integrity are of great significance for the entire 
European continent. 
  The head of the National Security Council expressed 
confidence that the forthcoming official visit by Ukraine's 
Minister of Foreign Affairs A. Zlenko will give a further 
impetus to Ukrainian-Polish relations in all spheres. 
  It is planned to discuss, during the visit, an extensive 
range of issues of bilateral cooperation within the framework of 
the NATO "Partnership for Peace" program. 

</TEXT>

