<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pawlak Expected To Approve Rosati Nomination </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2303113794 Warsaw RZECZPOSPOLITA in Polish 23 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> WS2303113794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw RZECZPOSPOLITA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by E.K.: "Prime Minister Gave Assurances to </F>
Coalition; Dariusz Rosati Finally Accepted"] 
  [Text] Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak is today expected to 
forward to the Belweder a motion requesting the appointment of 
Dariusz Rosati to the post of deputy prime minister and finance 
minister. 
  "We have received such an assurance from the coalition," 
said 
Aleksander Kwasniewski, following the Tuesday [22 March] session 
of the coalition's leadership. 
  As he was leaving the headquarters of the Polish Peasant 
Party, Prime Minister Pawlak merely stated that a press 
conference would be held on Wednesday. It can be expected, 
therefore, that he will officially announce the decision he 
reached yesterday. 
  Apart from the prime minister and the leader of the 
Democratic Left Alliance, also participating in the coalition 
meeting were Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy, Senate Speaker Adam 
Struzik, Deputy Prime Minister Wlodzimierz Cimoszewicz, Michal 
Strak, head of the Office of the Council of Ministers, and Jerzy 
Szmajdzinski, general secretary of Social Democracy of the 
Polish Republic. 
  One of the issues discussed was, among other topics, the 
report from the National Council of Radio and Television. 
  The coalition has not yet agreed on a joint position on this 
issue because not all of the deputies have had time to 
familiarize themselves with the council's report. 
  "Evaluation of the report calls for a serious discussion, 
which will be held at the end of April or the beginning of May," 
said Kwasniewski. 

</TEXT>

