<H3> <TI>   Serbs Continue To Violate Sarajevo Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203194694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2203194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The aggressor continues to violate the Sarajevo 
cease-fire by opening fire from various types of infantry 
weapons. They opened barrage fire toward Marin Dvor from the 
direction of the (?Bosut) Barracks. Chetnik snipers also 
attacked the district of Dobrinja and Brekin Potok. One 
explosion of a cumulative mortar bomb was also registered. It 
was fired from [word indistinct] on Stup district. 
  The members of the United Nations Protection Forces came 
under fire from the aggressors' positions in Nedjarici again 
today. They responded in kind to the fire that came from Stup 
hill. This was reported by the Information Service of the 1st 
Army Corps. 

</TEXT>

