<H3> <TI>   CTV Acquires REUTER as Partner </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2103151194 Bratislava REPUBLIKA in Slovak 17 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> AU2103151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava REPUBLIKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "REUTER Partner in CTV"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--The Slovak CTV television company, 
which is seeking a license to broadcast in the Slovak Republic, 
has acquired another foreign partner. It is REUTER, the 
world-famous news agency. Besides acquiring a minority stake of 
a maximum of 15 percent, REUTER is also interested in 
participating in news production. The first foreign partner in 
CTV was the German Commerzbank, which remains its exclusive 
financial representative. The Slovak company retains a majority 
stake of 51 percent. 

</TEXT>

