<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Resolution To Submit EU Accession Bid Adopted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2203163294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1600 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2203163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National Assembly has adopted the government 
proposal for Hungary to submit its application for accession to 
the European Union. The parliament adopted the draft resolution 
on submitting the accession application with 233 votes in favor, 
zero votes against, and three abstentions. 
  It is possible that Hungary will submit its application to 
join the European Union as early as next Thursday, and Poland 
will probably do this at the same time, the Hungarian Foreign 
Ministry's state secretary said. Janos Martonyi was speaking to 
the MTI correspondent in Warsaw. He said that the main 
objective of his visit to Poland was to coordinate policy on 
European integration. 
  The state secretary observed that like the Hungarians, 
Polish 
foreign policy regards cooperation between the Visegrad 
countries to be important. 

</TEXT>

