<H3> <TI>   Court Changes Verdict on Ex-Politburo Members </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803161394 Tirana ATA in English 1116 GMT 18 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1803161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 18 (ATA) -- The Supreme Court of 
Appeal decided to change the decision of the Court of Appeal for 
10 former senior officials of the Party of Labour of Albania, 
the spokesman of the court said. 
  Just like the decision of the Tirana District Court, the new 
decision too considers guilty the following: Qirjako Mihali, 
Pali Miska, Besnik Bekteshi, Vangjel Cerrava, Prokop Murra, 
Llambi Gegprifti, Muho Asllani, Hajredin Celiku, Foto Cami, and 
Lenka Cuko for having violated the equality of citizens through 
the creation of privileges for themselves. In a second 
consideration of the case by the Court of Appeal, these former 
leaders were accused of the crime of abuse of office. The 
spokesman explains that the Supreme Court of Appeal changed the 
decision of the Court of Appeal and sent the case for another 
consideration by the first level court. 
  According to the decision of the Supreme Court of Appeal, 
the 
civil indictment will be dismissed by the obligation that all 
the defendants will pay back respective amounts of money to the 
Government Service Department. 
  Sentences for the defendants range from 4-7 years of 
imprisonment. 

</TEXT>

