<H3> <TI>   Berisha `Grateful' for German Support </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203180294 Tirana ATA in English 1106 GMT 22 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2203180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 22 (ATA) -- "All the possibilities 
exist for more intense relations in all fields between our two 
countries," President Berisha said in yesterday's meeting with 
German parliamentarians headed by Mr. Michael Glos. 
  Mr. Berisha said he was grateful to Germany and German 
parliament for their support to Albania from the very beginning 
of the democratic processes. President Berisha also called for 
the Germany's support for Albania's integration in the European 
institutions. 
  Mr. Berisha said Germany should make its contribution to a 
fair resolution to the crises in Balkans. "In this context," 
President Berisha said, "removal or facilitation in the UN 
embargo on Serbia would escalate the conflict and destabilize 
the situation in the region." 
  The German parliamentarians thanked President Berisha for 
the 
presentation of the situation in Albania. They highly 
appreciated the achievements of democracy in Albania and 
promised they will make their contribution to Albania in a 
concrete and effective assistance of Germany to it. 
  The German parliamentarians were received yesterday by the 
president of the Democratic Party, Eduard Selami. 

</TEXT>

