<H3> <TI>   Berov in `Good Condition,' To Return `Soon' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803121694 Sofia BTA in English 1325 GMT 18 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1803121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, March 18 (BTA) -- Prime Minister Lyuben 
Berov is in good condition a week after major by-pass surgery, 
the Council of Ministers said. His cardio-vascular system, as 
well as his other organs and systems, are functioning normally. 
  Berov's recovery is following the regular course, aided by 
postoperative treatment and exercise. In a conversation today 
with Yunal Lyutfi of the ethnic Turks' Movement for Rights and 
Freedoms the prime minister said he would be back to work soon. 
Lyutfi quoted Berov's words in an informal conversation in 
parliament after they had talked at the hospital of the Military 
Medical Academy. Berov takes eight steps every day. Twenty days 
after the operation he will move to Bankya near Sofia for 
further treatment. 

</TEXT>

