<H3> <TI>   Goncz Stresses Ties With Poland Before Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2203204394 Warsaw PAP in English 2022 GMT 22 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2203204394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, March 22 -- According to Hungarian 
President Arpad Goncz, Polish-Hungarian friendship is and will 
always be topical and the present political situation prompts 
Warsaw and Budapest to have even closer contacts than so far. 
The slogan: Poles and Hungarians are friends will always be 
topical, Goncz told Polish correspodents in Budapest on Tuesday, 
before his three-day visit to Warsaw, Poznan and Krakow to start 
on March 28. 
  Pointing to the will to become integrated with western 
Europe, common to Poland and Hungary, President Goncz said that 
Poland should be the closest and most important partner for 
Budapest. He stressed also the importance of the Visegrad group 
and said that he believed in the concept of central Europe, 
although it could be interpreted differently. 
  Referring to his planned meetings with Polish politicians, 
particularly with President Lech Walesa and Prime Minister 
Waldemar Pawlak, the head of the Hungarian state said that 
mutual presentation of views would be very important for the 
better understanding of both countries. 

</TEXT>

