<H3> <TI>   Ukraine's Zlenko Visits, Meets With Officials </TI></H3>
<H4>   Stresses National Security Issues </H4>
<F P=102> LD2203163494 Warsaw PAP in English 1551 GMT 22 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2203163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, March 22 -- Visiting Foreign Minister of 
Ukraine Anatoliy Zlenko said on Tuesday the strategic base of 
Polish-Ukraine partnership relations should be both countries' 
national security. 
  "Ukraine and Poland are two big partners in our subregion, 
and the deepening of their mutual relations may have a 
significant meaning for the entire region, and may become an 
example of jointly naming and solving concrete problems," said 
Zlenko during a press conference on the second and last day of 
his visit to Poland. 
  The Ukrainian guest said he is satisfied with the talks with 
Polish politicians. He said he discussed with Polish Foreign 
Minister Andrzej Olechowski Ukraine's possible access to the 
France-German-Poland axis. 
  He said he also discussed the filling of the security vacuum 
in central and eastern Europe and the creation of a joint 
collective security system. 

</TEXT>

