<H3> <TI>   Polls Reveal HZDS Support Rising Again </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203144494 Prague CTK in English 1322 GMT 22 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2203144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 22 (CTK) -- The popularity of 
deposed premier Vladimir Meciar's Movement for a Democratic 
Slovakia (HZDS) is once again on the rise, Slovak Radio reported 
today. 
  Citing its own poll conducted March 11-16, immediately after 
Meciar's fall from power, the station said that if parliamentary 
elections were held today, 26 per cent of voters would vote 
HZDS. The Democratic Left Party (SDL) would trail with only 11 
percent, the Christian Democratic Movement (KDH) with 6 percent, 
and the Association of Workers (SD), which recently split from 
the SDL, with five percent. Fifteen percent of voters were 
undecided for any party and 11 per cent said they would not vote. 

</TEXT>

