<H3> <TI>   Money Allocated for Serbian `Colonization' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203180494 Tirana ATA in English 1112 GMT 22 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2203180494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 22 (ATA) -- The Belgrade's Serbian 
authorities recently reported they have allocated 400 million DM 
[German marks] for the construction of buildings and houses for 
Serbian settlers envisaged to be brought to Kosova. 
  [number indistinct] Albanians have been suspended so far 
from 
their jobs and are being replaced by Serbians [word indistinct] 
in Kosova from Serbia, Bosnia, or Croatia. 300,000 Albanians 
have immigrated during the recent years and forced by the 
Serbian repression they have emigrated in Western Europe. There 
are so far 30,000 Serbian settlers in Kosova and this number is 
increasing. New settlers, who keep coming to Kosova, have been 
given houses and agricultural land. 
  The Kosova colonization is laid as primary task in the 
Milosevic nationalist program for an unique Serbia. Last week, 
Serbian authorities in Prishtina decided to grant Serbians 50 
construction sites. 

</TEXT>

