<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Leaders Brief UNHCR on Serb `Terror' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203180694 Tirana ATA in English 1109 GMT 22 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2203180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 22 (ATA) -- The UN High Commissariat 
for Refugees (UNHCR) held on March 18 a meeting devoted to 
Kosova and Albanian refugees. Fifty jurists of the commissariat 
and two members of the DLK [Kosova Democratic Alliance] 
Presidency, the Benelux branch, Ramadan Gashi and Gani Azemi 
took part in the meeting. 
  The DLK representatives pointed out that due to the terror 
and continuous violence in Kosova, many Albanian youngsters are 
forced to leave their country and seek temporary asylum in the 
Western states. Moreover they are under the Serbian threat for 
violently being called up in the Serbian Army and then sent to 
Bosnia and Croatia. 
  Referring to this campaign, Mr. Gashi and Mr. Azemi said 
that 
"the Albanian people in Kosova are under a permanent threat, 
thus concrete measures must be undertaken in their defence." 

</TEXT>

