<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   German Defense Ministry Delegation Visits </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2103205494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2103205494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At Senate headquarters today a delegation from 
Germany's Defense Ministry led by State Secretary for Defense 
Bernd Wilz was received by the chairmen of the defense councils 
of the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies, Radu Timofte and 
Petre Roman. 
  After briefly presenting the bills that have been already 
passed or that are still to be passed by parliament in the 
domain of defense, public order, and national security, Timofte 
and Roman emphasized the importance of Romania's military 
cooperation with NATO structures, each NATO country, and 
especially Germany. As a sign of the democratization of our 
country's defense structures, Timofte outlined the setting up of 
the National Defense Collegium. 
  The head of the German military delegation stressed the 
interest of his country in a good military cooperation with 
Romania, mentioning within that context that over the current 
year about 40 various cooperation projects are to be 
accomplished, four Romanian officers are currently studying in 
Germany, and that the [word indistinct] of the National Defense 
Ministry, as well as the needs of the Romanian Armed Forces will 
be satisfied to a great extent from the equipment of the army of 
the former German Democratic Republic. 
  In conclusion Wilz appreciated the fact that Romania is on 
the right track regarding the parliament's control over the 
defense, public order, and national security institutions. He 
added that on Wednesday [23 March] a delegation of the Bundestag 
Defense Commission is to arrive in Romania, reports our 
correspondent Dan Preda. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

