<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Melescanu Discusses Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203123294 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2203123294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Teodor Melescanu has received 
Bernd Wilz, parliamentary state secretary in charge of defense 
in the Bundestag, accompanied by Klaus Franke, chairman of the 
German-Romanian Friendship Parliamentary Group. 
  In their discussion the two sides focused on continuing the 
political dialogue at various levels and on relations between 
the two armies. They also examined ways and means to put the 
Partnership for Peace plan into practice, as well as a number of 
international issues, including the situation in former 
Yugoslavia and in the Russian Federation. 
  The two sides also discussed the visits a number of German 
figures will pay to Romania this year: Minister of Defense 
Volker Ruehe, whose visit is scheduled to take place at the 
beginning of April; Foreign Minister Affairs Klaus Kinkel; 
Carl-Dieter Spranger, federal minister of economic cooperation; 
and Bundestag President Rita Suessmuth. 
  Romania's relations with Germany are of particular 
importance 
within the context in which Germany is broaching relations with 
the states in the (?Balkan) area pragmatically and 
indiscriminately, said the spokesman of the Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs, Mircea Geoana, to our reporter Eugen Baboi at the end 
of the talks. 

</TEXT>

