<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army-Defense Ministry Coordination Criticized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403103294 Sofia 24 CHASA in Bulgarian 19 Mar 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> AU2403103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia 24 CHASA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Editorial commentary: "Our Army Looks Toward Russia, Our </F>
Generals Toward the United States"] 
  [Text] In sending three delegations to the United States 
at the same time our military chiefs have broken a record. 
  Ostensibly, our arms are Russian, we cry out for spare parts 
from Moscow and Kiev, the army does not have a penny to its 
name, and yet our generals constantly look toward the West. 
  The chief of General Staff returned from Brussels and left 
immediately for NATO's Atlantic headquarters in Norfolk. All 
right, in Belgium we at least have certain interests -- we are 
about to send our representatives to NATO headquarters -- but 
what business do we have with the Atlantic? 
  In addition, the fact that three delegations are heading for 
the United States shows that there is apparently no coordination 
between the General Staff and the Ministry of Defense in 
anything related to the Army cuts and visits abroad. 

</TEXT>

