<H3> <TI>   Serb Sources Deny Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2303214794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 2122 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2303214794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Banja Luka, 23 Mar (TANJUG) -- A UN convoy bound for 
Maglaj was stopped today near the village of Crna Rijeka west of 
Novi Seher because the road was mined, we have learned from 
Srpska republic army sources. 
  The convoy was stopped and all personnel were warned that 
the 
road was mined. The drivers and crew left the vehicles, and the 
Srpska republic army provided safety for the convoy to avoid the 
possibility of theft and plunder. 
  According to Serb military sources, claims published by 
foreign media that the Srpska army plundered the convoy were 
incorrect. This is yet another attempt at vilifying and 
accusing the Serb side of a lack of cooperation, the Srpska 
republic army sources say. 

