<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croats Prepare for Constitutional Assembly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2303160594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1400 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2303160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Political representatives of the Croat people in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina are making preparations for the forthcoming 
assembly sessions which will determine the future of this 
republic. Zdenko Vranjes reports from Mostar for Croatian Radio: 
  [Vranjes] The leadership of the Croat republic of 
Herceg-Bosna and Croat deputies are carrying out preparations 
for two forthcoming sessions -- important sessions indeed -- of 
the chamber of deputies of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna 
scheduled for Saturday and the historic constitutional 
[ustavotvoran] assembly of federal Bosnia-Herzegovina which is 
expected to take place in Sarajevo on Monday and Tuesday. 
Kresimir Zubak [president of the presidential council of 
Herceg-Bosna] has told Croatian Radio the following: 
  [begin recording] [Zubak] [words indistinct] this session of 
the constitutional assembly scheduled for Monday 28 March. We 
have scheduled, prior to this, a session of the chamber of 
deputies of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna at which we 
should inform the deputies about the documents we adopted in 
Washington and prepared in Vienna. 
  All deputies to the chamber of deputies of the Croat 
republic 
of Herceg-Bosna are also deputies to the constitutional 
assembly. This assembly of Herceg-Bosna is going to formulate 
final standpoints and instruct the deputies at the session of 
the constitutional assembly on Monday and Tuesday. 
  [Vranjes] Will all the deputies from the ranks of the Croat 
people take part in the constitutional assembly in Sarajevo on 
Monday? Has this been prepared and agreed yet? 
  [Zubak] All technical details relating to this have not been 
agreed yet. I believe that today or tomorrow we will agree on 
every technical detail. We are of the opinion that all the 
deputies from the ranks of the Croat people who were deputies to 
the former assembly of Bosnia-Herzegovina should be present and 
vote. It is a known fact that a constitution may be adopted by 
a consensus of two peoples. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

