<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNHCR Aid Convoy Leaves for Tuzla </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2303184894 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1807 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2303184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zvornik, March 23 (TANJUG) -- A convoy of the U.N. 
High Commessariat for Refugees (UNHCR) on Wednesday crossed the 
territory of the Bosnian Serb republic (RS) on its way for 
Moslem-held Tuzla, northeast Bosnia, Bosnian Serb military 
sources in Zvornik said. 
  The 13 truck convoy was carrying 104 tonnes of flour. 
  Another relief aid convoy was also scheduled to leave for 
Tuzla, but the UNHCR team failed to return from a previous 
humanitarian mission, the Zvornik authorities were told. 
  Bosnian Serb military sources said that the fact that since 
their very start the humanitarian land convoys for Tuzla have 
crossed Bosnian Serb territory safely and unhindered, gives rise 
for doubts in the humanitarian reasons for the opening of the 
Tuzla airport. 
  The sources said that the land routes enable the efficient 
ferrying of much bigger quantities of relif aid to Tuzla than 
via the air bridge. 

</TEXT>

