<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows More Trust in UN Than NATO </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2303144294 Bratislava REPUBLIKA in Slovak 19 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU2303144294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava REPUBLIKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Slovaks Trust the United Nations"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--The Public Opinion Research Center at 
the Slovak Defense Ministry has conducted a survey. From the 
point of view of the security of Slovakia, 25.6 percent of the 
respondents trust the UN most, 12.4 percent the European 
security system, and 11.4 percent NATO membership. The citizens 
showed most trust in the UN--53.9 percent--while 23.1 percent 
trust NATO. Of the respondents, 44.7 percent were in favor of 
Slovakia's joining NATO, while 20.2 percent opposed it. The 
remaining 35.1 percent could not decide. NATO was described as 
more or less the only guarantor of European security by 55.4 
percent, while 25.2 percent disagreed with this. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

