<H3> <TI>   Dutch Soldiers Prefer Czech Submachine Guns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403102894 Prague CESKY DENIK in Czech 22 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2403102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CESKY DENIK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "luv": "The Czech Submachine Guns Used in the </F>
Exercises Suit the Dutch Soldiers Just Fine"] 
  [Text] Cesky Krumlov--The first joint exercises of the 
Czech Republic Army and the Armed Forces of the Kingdom of the 
Netherlands continue in Boletice in the Cesky Krumlov region 
[southern Bohemia]. 
  The joint exercises of 120 members of the Chrudim 
rapid-deployment battalion of the Czech Republic Army and 32 
Dutch marines are based on the closest possible contact and 
mutual exchange of information. In addition to shooting 
practice, a part of the exercises consists of tactical drills in 
the siege of areas occupied by terrorist units. Spikerman von 
Weezelenburg, commander of the Dutch marines, is currently on an 
inspection visit of the exercises. "It is the first specific 
action stemming from the Partnership for Peace plan," Major Ales 
Vodehnal, commander of the exercises, told CESKY DENIK. He 
added that, despite the Dutch being a professional unit with a 
high standard of training, they consider the Czech submachine 
guns, for instance, to be of better quality than their own. 

</TEXT>

