<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Committee Opposes Serb Territorial Concessions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2303161094 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2303161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Committee of the Patriotic League of Belgrade 
University at its session today discussed the general position 
of other countries, particularly the Serbian lands. It 
concluded, among other things, that it should address the Serbs 
in the republic of Serbian Krajina and the Srpska republic. The 
address, which was signed by student Bratislav Zarkovic on 
behalf of the committee, states the following: 
  In the negotiations on territorial demarcation currently 
under way, the representatives of the Serbian people must not 
and cannot make under any conditions territorial and other 
concessions that would in any way harm the interests of the 
[Serbian] lands. Regardless of the pressure that the Serbian 
people are being subjected to by the international community 
during these negotiations, territorial concessions cannot be 
allowed because the territories on which the Serbs live are 
historically theirs. Therefore, this generation of negotiators 
has no right to give up these territories under any condition. 
  The address also states that it is high time for all 
patriotic forces in the Srpska republic and the republic of 
Serbian Krajina to unite because this is in the interest of all 
Serbs in all regions and in the interest of preserving their 
biological survival. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-9417 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu057_y_94007" </HT>


