<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs `Torture' Former Albanian Army Officers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403083394 Tirana RILINDJA in Albanian 23 Mar 94 p 16 </F>
<F P=103> AU2403083394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana RILINDJA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Serbian Interrogators Even Use </F>
Chemical Substances"] 
  [Text] Ismet Veliqi, Avdi Behrami, and Azem Gashi, former 
military officers and members of the former people's defense 
forces of Skenderaj [Srbica], whom the Serbian police arrested a 
few days ago, are being brutally maltreated in Mitrovice Prison, 
the Information Committee of the Kosova Democratic Alliance's 
Mitrovice branch reports. 
  It is reported that they are being tortured at night by 
employees of the Serbian security services, who come specially 
from Prishtina. It is reported that the Serbian interrogators 
are using chemical substances, electric prods, and other methods 
to torture the former Albanian officers. The detainees' 
condition is very serious. Torture during the investigation 
process suggests the preparation of another political show 
trial, this time of former Albanian Army officers in Kosova. 

</TEXT>

