<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Appoints Adviser, Military Chiefs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2403143194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1200 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2403143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman today decided to 
appoint Professor Djordje Pribicevic as special adviser to the 
president of the republic. President Tudjman has also relieved 
Major General Slobodan Praljak, the head of the military office 
of the president of the republic, of his duties, because he is 
taking up the duties of head of the Croatian Information and 
Culture Center. 
  The president has appointed Maj. Gen. Zvonimir Cervenko, the 
hitherto deputy chief of general staff for the Home Guard, as 
head of the military office. President Tudjman has decided to 
relieve Brigadier Drago Krpina, head of the political department 
of the Ministry for Defense of his duties and demote him to 
reserve service. Brigadier Ivan Tolj has been appointed to this 
post. 

</TEXT>

