<H3> <TI>   Martic: Assembly `Leading State Into Chaos' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2303204394 Belgrade RTB Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2303204394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade RTB Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Milan Martic, president of the republic of </F>
Serbian Krajina, on Knin Television on 23 March -- recorded] 
  [Text] Milan Martic, president of the republic of Serbian 
Krajina [RSK], today addressed RSK citizens and deputies of the 
RSK Assembly via Knin Television. Here is Milan Martic's 
statement that we received from Knin: 
  [Begin Martic recording] Citizens of the RSK, the current 
work of the republican parliament, which is primarily 
characterized by some political divisions and a one-sided 
imposition of the coalitions' stands, is leading the state into 
total chaos and anarchy. 
  As president of the RSK, I will not allow this. In these 
exceptionally difficult times for our state, when, in addition 
to all the other pressures and difficulties, we are achieving 
significant results on the international political scene, we are 
encountering obstacles that are exclusively the consequence of 
such work by the assembly. As president of the republic and the 
supreme commander of the armed forces, I will not allow the RSK 
to become a (?battlefield) for political showdowns between 
political parties [word indistinct]. 
  Citizens of the RSK, fighters, workers, and pensioners, I 
demand that you raise your voice to remove the obstacles caused 
by the work of the parliament, to reexamine the mandate you have 
loaned to some deputies, and to call them to account. 
  The respected deputies must know that they have been elected 
by you and that they are only accountable to you and not the 
political leaders whose dictates they are now implementing. 

</TEXT>

