<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   RSK Accuses Croatia of Dumping Toxic Waste </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103161594 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1530 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Knin, March 21 (TANJUG)--The republic of Serb 
Krajina (RSK) has information, detailed maps and documentation 
confirming that Croatia is depositing nuclear waste and toxic 
chemicals in western Slavonia, RSK Foreign Minister Slobodan 
Jarcevic told TANJUG Monday. 
  Jarcevic said that the deposits were being made on Mt Papuk 
in an area 35 times 50 kilometers, that is now ethnically 
cleansed from Serbs, in four locations identified so far: 
Straza, Tucak, Bilo and Lom. 
  The RSK was formed in 1991 in parts of the former Yugoslav 
Republic of Croatia populated by Serbs in response to the 
Croatian forcible secession from the former Yugoslav Federation 
and has been a U.N. Protected Area (UNPA) since March 1992. 
  The RSK Foreign Ministry has conveyed this information to 
the 
co-chairmen of the Conference on the Former Yugoslavia and U.N. 
member countries that have their troops within the UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces], Jarcevic said adding that they had not shown 
any particular interest. 
  Jarcevic said that the nuclear waste and the poisonous 
chemicals originate from Germany and are transported through 
Austria and Hungary. 
  According to further information Bosnian Moslem leader Alija 
Izetbegovic has also promised his patrons and the initiators of 
the new world order locations for depositing their nuclear waste 
and toxic chemicals on Serb territory stretching from Kupres to 
Drvar. 
  It is also reported in Knin that Greece fears that similar 
engagements were undertaken by the president of The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia Kiro Gligorov and information 
about Germany's deposit of its toxic waste in Albania near the 
border with the F.R. of Yugoslavia has already been partly 
revealed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

