<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Mortar Shells Fall on Sarajevo Region </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2303154494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2303154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the Sarajevo region, sniper fire was registered 
in the Brijesce district, which was hit from the direction of 
[Serb-occupied] Rajlovac. Mortar bombs launched from Nedzarici 
[Serb-occupied western suburb of Sarajevo] fell on Stup and the 
region of (Lise) was hit with hand grenades and mortars. This 
has been reported by the Information Service of the 1st Corps of 
the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army. 

</TEXT>

