<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Klaus Leaves for Three-Day Visit to Finland </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2403182194 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1700 
GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2403182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [Announcer] Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus left for 
a three-day official visit to Finland late this afternoon. 
Miroslav Konvalina reports from Ruzyne Airport: 
  [Konvalina] We do not have any problems in bilateral 
contacts 
with Finland. On the contrary, Vaclav Klaus will affirm our 
permanent interest in this northern country. He gave us his 
reasons a few weeks ago, after returning from Norway, which so 
far was the last Scandinavian country he visited. 
  [Begin Klaus recording] We should not forget that the Czech 
Republic, with its geographic size and number of inhabitants, 
must logically seek partners not from among the superpowers, as 
we thought at a certain time in the past. Norway and Finland 
are our natural partners. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

