<H3> <TI>   Zieleniec Discusses Cooperation, EU With Dutch </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2403171994 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1400 
GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2403171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dutch Foreign Minister Peter Kooijmans, who has 
joined the delegation of the Netherlands' Queen Beatrix in 
Prague, had talks today with his counterpart, Josef Zieleniec. 
Klara Stejskalova reports: 
  [Stejskalova] The Czech foreign affairs minister welcomed, 
in 
the beginning, the visit of the Netherlands royal couple to our 
country. The two ministers then agreed that mutual relations 
between the Czech Republic and the Netherlands were good. That 
is why questions of multilateral cooperation were the main topic 
of their conversation. 
  They talked, above all, about the European Union [EU], which 
the Czech Republic intends to join in the future. According to 
the two foreign ministers, the EU is currently undergoing 
dramatic moments, as confirmed by the current crisis on the 
question of the lower blocking minority by percent required by 
Britain. The emergent crisis only confirms the need for 
discussion on the future philosophy of the EU. 
  The agenda of the Dutch-Czech talks also included questions 
on the Partnership for Peace program and overall security in 
Europe. 

</TEXT>

