<H3> <TI>   Serbs Rule Out Joining Croat-Muslim Federation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2403181294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1750 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2403181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 24 Mar (TANJUG) -- The deputies of the 
People's Assembly of the Srpska republic today adopted a report 
on the course of the Geneva talks and the Serb delegation's 
stances on the negotiations. 
  The conclusions are that the platform on future talks 
remains 
the same and that any possibility of the Srpska republic joining 
the Croat-Muslim federation is ruled out. However, the 
possibility of forming links with the newly created entities 
remains open, but only after the strategic interests of the Serb 
nation are realized. 
  The session of the Srpska republic people's assembly resumed 
work at 1800 with discussion of internal policy. This part of 
the session is held behind closed doors. 

</TEXT>

