<F P=102>  AU2403153394 Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI in Serbo-Croatian 24 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2403153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Federal Republic of Yugoslavia's Army </F>
-- to Bosnia!"] 
  [Text] "The roots of Serbhood are in Sarajevo, it is 
Serbian ethnic territory. The Muslims are probably counting on 
the time when they will again mix Serbs and Muslim, thus making 
Sarajevo theirs. But that will not be accepted. 
  "I believe in the possibility of Sarajevo one day becoming a 
unified city, but it will not belong to the Muslims, but to the 
Srpska republic," claims Momcilo Krajisnik, chairman of the 
Srpska republic assembly, in an interview for SVET. "We will 
never agree to the deployment of German or Turkish troops, 
because they are still in the service of imperialism. The 
Russian soldiers here can be compared to the troops from other 
Islamic countries [as published], against whom we have nothing 
-- except for Turkey. If Turkey succeeds in pushing its 
proposal through the United Nations, we shall ask that 
Yugoslavia send its troops to Bosnia," says Krajisnik. 

</TEXT>

