Muslim-controlled part of Novi Travnik. Zdenko Vranjes reports 
in more detail. 
  [Vranjes] This morning Serb artillery attacked the 
Muslim-controlled part of Novi Travnik. Fierce artillery 
clashes between the Serb and the Muslim forces are still raging. 
According to this town's people, the separation lines between 
the HVO and the Muslim army are absolutely quiet. 
  Mostar is also quiet. Last night there were some isolated 
provocations from infantry weapons in the town center. In 
Uskoplje [Gornji Vakuf] Muslim and Croat representatives are 
today discussing the further exchange of POW's in keeping with 
the all-for-all principle. The exchange of POW's from central 
Bosnia remains to be carried out. 
  Until the next elections the Croatian Democratic Union 
[Hrvatska Demokratska Zajednica] of Bosnia-Herzegovina is the 
only legal representative of Croat interests in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. The Croat National Council from Sarajevo or 
any other minority group of Croat deputies has no right to act 
on behalf of all Croat deputies and the entire Croat people in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, the Bosnia-Herzegovina HDZ [Croatian 
Democratic Community] said in its statement today. 

