<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drnovsek Seeks Replacement of Defense Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2503042094 Belgrade TANJUG in English 0058 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2503042094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ljubljana, March 24 (TANJUG) -- Slovenian Prime 
Minister Janez Drnovsek has asked parliament to replace Defence 
Minister Janez Jansa. In a statement for the public released on 
Thursday, Drnovsek accused the defence minister of overstepping 
his authority and violating the republican constitution and 
elementary human rights. 
  Political circles in Ljubljana have indicated that Minister 
Jansa might resort to repressive protection of his office, in 
which, as assessed, he would have the support of part of the 
military leadership. The Slovenian police raised the degree of 
alert of its force on Thursday evening. 
  Jansa is the idol of the Slovenian extreme nationalist right 
and, as his followers often point out, most deserving for 
Slovenia's independence which followed a clash with the former 
Yugoslav People's Army. 
  Several parties, associations, groups of citizens and 
individuals have demanded the defence minister's resignation 
over the past few days. 

</TEXT>

