<H3> <TI>   Further on Replacement Request </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403215594 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
2100 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2403215594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a letter he sent today, Prime Minister Janez 
Drnovsek informed the Social Democratic Party of Slovenia that 
he had sent the State Chamber his proposal on the replacement of 
Defense Minister Janez Jansa. Namely, the government commission 
investigating into the Smolnikar case has established that 
members of the Defense Ministry have overstepped their powers. 
Therefore, the defense minister must take responsibility for 
that activity. According to Drnovsek, permitting such activity 
would mean deviating from the rule of law. The prime minister 
suggests that the Social Democratic Party should continue 
participating in the government coalition. 

</TEXT>

