<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a letter to Herman Rigelnik, chairman of the 
State Chamber, Prime Minister Dr. Janez Drnovsek proposed that 
the State Chamber should relieve Janez Jansa of his duties as 
minister of defense on the basis of Article 112 of the 
Constitution of the Republic of Slovenia and Article 19 of the 
Law on Government of the Republic of Slovenia. The prime 
minister suggests that the State Chamber appoint Jelko Kacin as 
minister of defense. Prime Minister Drnovsek also suggested 
that the release of duty and appointment be carried out as soon 
as possible. 

