<H3> <TI>   Jansa Protests Dismissal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2503093894 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
2100 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2503093894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Janez Jansa, president of the Social Democratic 
Party of Slovenia, said in an open letter to Prime Minister 
Drnovsek that he has received his letter concerning his 
replacement as defense minister. 
  Janez Jansa rebukes Prime Minister Drnovsek as the 
government 
commission that was investigating the Smolnikar case did not 
study all the necessary material. He also asks Janez Drnovsek 
how the government has acted in other cases in which there has 
been an overstepping of authority. 
  According to him, the prime minister proposed the 
replacement 
before the meeting of the parliamentary inquiry commission and 
in the midst of a media lynching. Jansa believes that Drnovsek, 
in this way, prevented the investigation into the background of 
unlawful activities in which individuals and groups have engaged 
for months. 
  The Presidency of the Social Democratic Party of Slovenia 
will discuss this issue tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

