<H3> <TI>   Christian Democrats Comment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2503094594 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
2100 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2503094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Executive Council of the Slovene Christian 
Democrats, in a statement for the public, condemned any sort of 
use of violence in the fulfillment of political and ideological 
goals. 
  The Slovene Christian Democrats, therefore, call upon all 
those who have violated fundamental moral and ethical principles 
to leave the Slovene political scene. 
  As the second most powerful parliamentary party, the 
Christian Democrats wish to contribute toward appeasement, 
stability, and progress, because divisions cannot be the guiding 
star of the young Slovene state, which was also confirmed by the 
incident in Depala Vas and recent statements by President Milan 
Kucan in Nova Gorica. 
  In cases of abuse of power, the Christian Democrats also 
expect the resignation of incumbent ministers. 
  If it transpires that the president of the republic has also 
been involved in the recent events, the Christian Democrats will 
demand his resignation, too. 

</TEXT>

