<H3> <TI>   FRY Files Complaint Against NATO </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2303114794 Paris AFP in English 1143 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2303114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Hague, March 23 (AFP) -- Yugoslavia filed a 
complaint against NATO with the International Court of Justice 
[ICJ], accusing its member states of violating the UN charter by 
threatening to use force in Bosnia, a source at the court said 
Wednesday [23 March]. 
  The rump Yugoslavia -- Serbia and Montenegro -- said NATO 
had 
used the threat of force without the required authorization of 
the UN Security Council. 
  Yugoslavia's suit cited the decision taken by the North 
Atlantic Treaty Organization at a Feburary 9 meeting in Brussels 
that warned Bosnian Serbs to withdraw heavy guns from Sarajevo 
or face NATO air strikes. 

</TEXT>

