<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gligorov Seeks EU Help in Dispute With Greece </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2403190394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1800 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2403190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov has sent a letter 
to European Union [EU] President Jacques Delors warning that 
during recent weeks Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] has been left to face the Greek economic 
embargo and the hermetically closed borders with Greece alone. 
Gligorov stresses that this could result in a dramatic economic 
destabilization of Macedonia, and consequently of the overall 
situation in the region. The Macedonian president goes on to 
say that the EU must find a solution to this problem, and notes 
the EU's slowness, lack of determination and unequal treatment 
of the two sides. At the end of his letter to Jacques Delors, 
Gligorov stresses that if the problem with Athens is not solved, 
Macedonia will have to initiate a discussion of the Greek 
embargo in the Security Council. 

</TEXT>

