<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two British Soldiers Wounded in Serb Shelling </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2503104094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1000 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2503104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Two British soldiers have been wounded in the Serb 
shelling of Bugojno, a British UN forces spokesman in Bugojno 
has announced. Around 0630 this morning, Serb artillery fired a 
number of shells on Bugojno, one of which hit the local UNPROFOR 
[UN Protection Forces] base. 
  Serb artillery shelled Travnik throughout the night. The 
[Croatian Defense Council] Stjepan Tomasevic brigade has said 
that Serb artillery was intensely shelling Muslim parts of 
Travnik. 
  The cease-fire has been observed by the Croat and the Muslim 
sides. 

</TEXT>

