<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Bosnia-Herzegovina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Silajdzic Wants Karadzic, Milosevic `Punished' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403110194 Hamburg STERN in German 24 Mar 94 p 228 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2403110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg STERN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris </F>
Silajdzic by Mario R. Dederichs; place and date not given: 
"Punishing the Instigators"] 
  [Text] [Dederichs] Will the agreement between the Croats 
and Bosnians finally bring peace for Bosnia? 
  [Silajdzic] It is a very important step to ending the 
conflict between two peoples that have coexisted in an exemplary 
manner for centuries. The war has destroyed a great deal of 
confidence, but in the end we will have to live together. 
  [Dederichs] Why was the agreement signed in Washington? 
  [Silajdzic] The United States has made a decisive 
contribution. I hope that it will continue its efforts because 
the Europeans are currying favor with the Serbs and rewarding 
aggression by recognizing conquests. 
  [Dederichs] Which Europeans? 
  [Silajdzic] The appeasement started in London and was 
completed in Moscow. The Germans were ready to help but were 
not always consistent. Germany has provided valuable assistance 
for our refugees. 
  [Dederichs] The European Union has demanded that the Bosnian 
Serbs should give up some of their territory. Is that not 
sufficient? 
  [Silajdzic] The principle of not recognizing occupied 
territories remains hollow if it is not implemented everywhere. 
  [Dederichs] The United Nations wants to prosecute the war 
criminals. 
  [Silajdzic] Culprits from all the ethnic groups must be 
punished, not only the criminals but the instigators, too, those 
who are responsible for "ethnic cleansing." 
  [Dederichs] Including the Serbian leaders Karadzic or 
Milosevic? 
  [Silajdzic] They must also be punished! We all must face up 
to the truth, otherwise 1994 will be like 1939. A total of 
16,000 children have been killed in the war in Bosnia. We know 
who is responsible. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-9531 </DOCNO>
