<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Welcomes U.S. Arms Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2303155694 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1414 GMT 23 Mar 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2303155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 23/3/1994 -- "The Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs has learned with great satisfaction of the U.S. 
President's decision to lift the restrictions on arms sales to 
Romania and other states in the region", reads a release 
presented to the news conference given on 23 March at the 
Foreign Ministry. "The Foreign Ministry welcomes the decision as 
being an important step both in the development of the 
Romanian-American cooperation in the military domain, and in the 
dynamics of the relations between Romania and the NATO, within 
the Partnership for Peace. 
  "The Foreign Ministry considers this decision made by the 
U.S. President to be a practical confirmation of the American 
stand according to which Romania's security is important for the 
United States security, being a matter of direct and material 
interest to the U.S. and the NATO", the release concludes. 

</TEXT>

