<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   SDL Forms Coalition for Local Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403164294 Prague CTK in English 1458 GMT 24 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2403164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 24 (CTK) -- The chairman of the 
Democratic Left Party (SDL), Peter Weiss, signed an agreement on 
cooperation in the November local elections with two minor 
left-wing parties today. 
  The coalition for the local elections is a first step for an 
agreement on cooperation in the general elections, Weiss told 
journalists. The coalition should offer citizens a "clear 
political alternative" and will receive support from partner 
parties in Western Europe, Weiss said. 
  The parties of the left coalition are the Social Democratic 
Party in Slovakia (SDSS), headed by Jaroslav Volf, and the 
Agricultural Movement (HZ), led by Jozef Klein. 
  The SDL has offered coalition membership also to the newly 
founded Slovak Entrepreneurs Association (ZPS), which however 
has decided to enter the elections independently. Polls show 
the ZPS to be Slovakia's fourth strongest party. With 4.8 
percent support among voters it would represent a significant 
boost to SDL popularity, currently rated at 11 percent. 

</TEXT>

