<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Dismisses Inspection Office Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403210994 Prague CTK in English 1955 GMT 24 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2403210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 24 (CTK) -- Parliament today 
dismissed by secret ballot the chairman of the Supreme 
Inspection Office (NKU), Marian Vanko, and its two vice 
chairmen, Petr Sokol and Marian Vrabec. 
  All three were associated with the former government of 
Vladimir Meciar, which fell in a no confidence vote earlier this 
month. Despite protests from the erstwhile opposition, which is 
today's government, Vanko was named to the top NKU post as a 
deputy of Meciar's Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS). 
  The vote was preceded by a stormy debate full of accusations 
that the NKU was misused under Meciar's government for political 
purposes and was "indirectly" run by the government office, 
headed by Meciar colleague Ivan Lexa. Others accused the new 
government of intending to do basically the same thing. 
  During the evening, members of the HZDS and its former 
coalition partner, the Slovak National Party (SNS), demonstrated 
in front of the parliament building. 

</TEXT>

