<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bukoshi Warns of Danger of `Large Conflict' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403121194 Tirana ATA in English 1127 GMT 24 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2403121194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 24 (ATA) -- "We appeal to the United 
Nations, the United States, the European Union and Russia to 
include Kosova completely in the peaceful process, because 
without the resolution of the Kosova question, there will be no 
peace in the Balkans," Mr. Bujar Bukoshi, premier of the 
republic of Kosova, said at the press conference in the UN 
headquarters in New York, on March 22. 
  Dr. Bukoshi, who started a three day visit to the United 
States, called on world authorities once more not to ignore the 
explosive situation in Kosova, but to undertake preventive 
measures before it will be late. 
  "We demand an international presence in Kosova which will 
help prevent Serbian abuses, which may lead to a large conflict 
with destructive consequences for the peace in the region", Mr. 
Bukoshi said. He reiterated that sanctions towards Serbia 
should be conditioned with the correct resolution of the Kosova 
question. Mr. Bukoshi said that the peaceful policy of the 
Kosova leadership may loose its credibility among the Albanian 
people on both sides, and this peaceful approach may be 
considered by Belgrade as a challenge to the increasing 
repression. 
  Mr. Bukoshi said that this stand of the Albanians may be 
considered by the international community as a reason to ignore 
the situation in Kosova. 
  "Kosova fulfills all premises to be an independent state 
like 
other republics of former Yugoslavia. It is the richest region 
and with sufficient human potential. We are not demanding 
unification with Albania and this is the greatest compromise we 
are as a people. [sentence as received] We do not demand a 
violent change of the borders," Mr. Bukoshi said in a response 
to a question "Is Kosova able to be an independent state and 
will it demand a unification with Albania?" 

</TEXT>

