<H3> <TI>   Serbs Training Army, Police Near Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403123294 Tirana ATA in English 1121 GMT 24 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2403123294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pristina, March 24 (ATA) -- Serbian army and police 
are training their units for four days now in Landovica, the 
Prizren district, near the border with Albania. 
  On March 23, military trucks and cannons of big calibers 
headed towards Djakova on the border with Albania. 
  On March 22, Serbian army forces stationed on the road that 
links Prizren with Kukes, city in the territory of Albania. 
Concentration and training of Serbian army and police forces 
have been noticed in other areas of Kosova as well. 

