<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Protests Shooting by Greek Border Unit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2603210894 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2603210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Greek Embassy Secretary (Toulupas) was summoned on 
26 March to the Foreign Ministry and was handed a note of 
protest regarding an event on 21 March 1994 in which a group of 
Albanians who had crossed the Albanian-Greek border were 
mistreated by the Greek border forces. 
  According to exact data, after pointing an automatic rifle 
at 
the chest of 21-year-old Albanian citizen Alfred Abaz Muco, a 
resident of Bubullime in Lushnje, a Greek soldier opened fire 
with no reason at all, causing his death. 
  The note stresses among other things that the Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Albania protests this ugly 
and tragic act, pointing out that such actions impair 
Albanian-Greek relations, create an unjustified situation of 
tension, and run counter to international norms and statements 
by the Greek authorities. 
  The note asks the Greek Government to give the necessary 
explanations about the circumstances of the event and take 
measures to condemn the culprits and prevent the repetition of 
such actions,which have occurred even in the past. 

</TEXT>

