<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former Prime Minister Sentenced to 14 Years </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2603184094 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1735 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2603184094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The trial of the defendants Fatos Nano, Sokrat 
Plaka, Robert Gjini, and Hasan Hallkja continued today. At the 
end of the summation the jury decided to declare defendant Fatos 
Nano guilty and sentence him to 14 years imprisonment; to 
declare defendant Sokrat Plaka guilty and sentence him to five 
years imprisonment; to declare defendant Robert Gjini guilty and 
sentence him to four years imprisonment; to declare defendant 
Hasan Hallkja guilty and sentence him to two years imprisonment. 
  The defendants also have the civil obligation to return to 
the Bank of Albania the amounts of money they are charged with 
taking. 
  After withdrawing for the decision, the judicial body set 30 
March 1994 at 0900 as a sufficient time for the four defendants 
to prepare their final statements and defense. 

</TEXT>

