<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Klaus on Speculation About Relocating RFE </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2803140094 Prague RUDE PRAVO in Czech 24 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2803140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague RUDE PRAVO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "ryc": "According to Klaus, the Deliberations </F>
About the RFE Moving Are Premature"] 
  [Text] Prague--Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus described on 
Wednesday [23 March] the deliberations on the conditions for 
moving the Free Europe Center (Radio Free Europe--RFE) from 
Munich to Prague as definitely premature because the U.S. party 
has not yet made its decision. Klaus said this before reporters 
in response to a RUDE PRAVO question on Wednesday. He added 
that the original promises that this matter "will be settled in 
October, December, February, and March are being constantly 
postponed." Klaus considers the transfer of the RFE from "a 
clearly government, state institution to another" an additional 
problem. Businessman Soros would "participate as a co-owner" in 
dealing with the latter problem. If this happened, the entire 
problem would move, according to the prime minister, to an 
entirely different level. 

</TEXT>

