<H3> <TI>   Bohemia Communist Party Expells 5 Deputies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2603144494 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1400 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2603144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At its session in Prague today, the Central 
Committee of the Communist Party of Bohemia [KSCM] expelled five 
deputies from the Left Bloc. They are: Jaroslav Ortman, 
chairman of the Left Bloc group and deputy chairman of the party 
Left Bloc, and members of the group Josef Hajek, Jaroslav 
Soural, Vlastislav Kuchar, and Zdenek Vorlicek. KSCM Chairman 
Miroslav Grebenicek said that the aforementioned deputies had 
practically departed from the Communist Party by initiating the 
emergence of the new party, the Left Bloc. 

