Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "r": "The Movement for a Democratic Slovakia </F>
Would Be Voted for by 26.4 Percent; 10.8 Percent Would Not Go to 
the Polls at All"] 
  [Text] Bratislava--Slovak Radio's Methodological Research 
Department carried out a public opinion survey from 11 to 16 
March, in which 1,025 respondents over age 18 were asked the 
following question: If new parliamentary elections were to be 
held this week, for which party or movement would you opt? The 
results can be gleaned from the table below: 


