<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meciar, Kovac Most Trusted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2503144594 Bratislava SLOVENSKY DENNIK in Slovak 24 Mar 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU2503144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SLOVENSKY DENNIK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "No Longer Relevant...."] </F>
  [Text] In a public opinion poll conducted by the 
Statistical Office of the Slovak Republic in March, 1,273 
citizens were asked to reply to the question: "Which politician 
active in the Slovak Republic enjoys your trust at present?" 
The replies acquired do not yet reflect the situation that 
arose after the 27th meeting of the National Council of the 
Slovak Republic with its consequences [passage of the vote of 
no-confidence in Vladimir Meciar's government and the 
appointment of a new government]. Compared with the poll 
carried out in early February, there was a visible increase in 
trust in President Michal Kovac and a reduction in the 
proportion of citizens who do not trust any politician. 


----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Trust in Representatives of Political Lifein Slovakia as Expressed by Citi-| 
|zens(in percent)                                                           | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|                  |Jan               |Feb               |Mar               | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Vladimir Meciar   |23                |22                |25                | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Michal Kovac      |23                |20                |25                | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Peter Weiss       |12                |15                |16                | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Ivan Gasparovic   |9                 |8                 |7                 | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Jan Carnogursky   |5                 |5                 |6                 | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Jozef Moravcik    |5                 |5                 |5                 | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Do not trust any  |41                |43                |31                | 
|politician        |                  |                  |                  | 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 



</TEXT>

