<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   HZDS Congress Stops Supporting President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2703195494 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1900 
GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2703195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The participants in the fourth congress of the 
Movement for a Democratic Slovakia [HZDS] in Presov have sent an 
open letter to Slovak President Michal Kovac. More from Martin 
Dorazin: 
  [Dorazin] We ask you to reassess your membership in the 
HZDS, 
states the letter addressed to Michal Kovac. Among other 
things, the letter from the congress of the strongest Slovak 
opposition party recalls that the current president used to be a 
leading representative of the HZDS, which nominated him to the 
Federal Assembly, later on as the assembly's chairman and then 
as president of the Slovak Republic. 
  The congress regrets having come to the conclusion that 
Michal Kovac has interrupted the continuity of the HZDS program. 
The HZDS can no longer support Kovac in the office of president 
of the Republic because of the way he carries out his 
presidential duties, because of the attempt to cause the HZDS's 
disintegration, and because of an unjustifiable attitude toward 
the government that founded the state, and for other reasons. 
This is all in the open letter. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
